Description: Fragment of oval, tapering handle of a pottery transport amphora at neck join. Clay fine salmon pink; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 102, 4 or 185, 2. Similar stamps from the Athenian Agora (e.g. SS8861, 10029) are termed Chian by Virigina Grace, but the profile of this handle is not typical of that fabric.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1641)
